cs.NI, cs.IT, cs.SY, cs.MM, cs.CR 

This paper deals with the challenge of accommodating Machine-to-Machine (M2M) applications and their requirements in LTE networks, which falls under the category of networked systems (cs.NI). The paper specifically focuses on the random access (RA) challenge in LTE networks, which involves contention resolution techniques, and thus could also be categorized under information theory (cs.IT) and control systems (cs.SY). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential overload and signaling storms that could occur in LTE networks due to the high density of devices, which could be considered under multimedia (cs.MM) and cryptography and security (cs.CR) categories.
